Class ForwardingListenerManager

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.google.common.collect.ForwardingObject
      • sk.stuba.fiit.perconik.core.ForwardingNameable
        • sk.stuba.fiit.perconik.core.services.ForwardingManager
          • sk.stuba.fiit.perconik.core.services.listeners.ForwardingListenerManager
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Nameable, ListenerManager, Manager

    public abstract class ForwardingListenerManager
extends ForwardingManager
implements ListenerManager
    A listener manager which forwards all its method calls to another listener manager. Subclasses should override one or more methods to modify the behavior of the backing listener manager as desired per the decorator pattern.

    Note that this class does not forward the equals and hashCode methods through to the backing object. See ForwardingObject for more details.

    Since:
    1.0
    Author:
    Pavol Zbell
